The new thing is the &lt;style&gt; element inside &lt;head&gt;; in it is a =
styling language called CSS (cascading style sheets). If you&#39;d like a gener=
al reference, head on over to &lt;https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/CSS=
&gt;.

The first rule selects all `html` elements (there should be only one!) =
and sets its color to a gray, its background to black, and centers all text=
 that&#39;s inside it.

The second rule selects all &lt;img&gt; elements that are the=
 first child of some container element. In our case, this&#39;ll be the first &lt;=
img&gt; element inside our lone &lt;div&gt; element. This &lt;img&gt; element then gets a =
fairly wide right margin of 5 ems (in CSSese: five times the height of the =
currently-used font).

Finally, I&#39;ve added a proper title to the page in th=
e &lt;title&gt; element.

